    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA363-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu pakaṟkuṟi vantu nīṅkun talaimakaṉait tōḻi “‘talaimakaḷai eṉṉai āṟṟuvikkum’ eṉṟu ākātō emperumāṉ. kavalātu celvatu yāṉ āṟṟuvikkumiṭattuk kavaṉṟāl nī āṟṟuvi” eṉac colliyatu. 2. kaiyuṟai nērnta tōḻi talaimakaṟkuk kaiyuṟai uraittatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is how the confidante said to HIM who left after having come to the day tryst: “Is it not, oh great one that [you think] ‘what will encourage HER?’ At the time I encourage [you] to go without anxiety, if you are anxious you will have the strength.” 2. It is also what the confidante who had accepted the gift said to HIM about the gift.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA363">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kaṇṭal vēlik kaḻicūḻ paṭappait</l>
<l>            teṇkaṭa ṉaṉāṭṭuc celvaṉ yāṉeṉa</l>
<l>            viyaṅkoṇ ṭēkiṉai yāyi ṉeṉaiyatūu</l>
<l>            muṟuviṉaik kacāvā vulaivil kammiyaṉ</l>
<l>            poṟiyaṟu piṇaikkūṭṭun tuṟaimaṇaṟ koṇṭu</l>
<l>            vammō vāḻi malinīrc cērppa</l>
<l>            paintaḻai citaiyak kōtai vāṭa</l>
<l>            naṉṉar mālai nerunai niṉṉoṭu</l>
<l>            cilavilaṅ kelvaḷai ñekiḻa</l>
<l>            valava ṉāṭṭuvōḷ cilampuñemirn taṉavē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>          If you were to take the order [and] go,</l>
<l rend="indent4">          saying</l>
<l rend="indent3">          “I go to the good land by the clear sea,</l>
<l rend="indent3">           with gardens surrounded by backwaters with mangrove fences,”</l>
<l>        come, oh man from the coast of abundant water,</l>
<l rend="indent">          bringing sand from the ghat, by which<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kūṭṭum</term>: here for once the <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> (modelled on the usual landscape description clause) is awkward, because the context (if we understand it correctly - I for one do not know why a goldsmith repairing a broken ornament would need sand from the ghat) requires a final infinitive.</note> the faultless(?) artisan puts</l>
<l rend="indent2">          the spotless links together [again], languishing not in the work he has.</l>
<l>        Crushed were the anklets of her who chased crabs,</l>
<l rend="indent">          so that [her] few shining light bangles became loose,</l>
<l rend="indent2">          with you yesterday, in the good evening,</l>
<l rend="indent">          so that the fresh foliage was spoilt [and] the garland faded.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
